com.kuka.scenegraph

Interface ITemplateService

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IGeometry

    public interface ITemplateService
    Enables creation of spatial objects using a collection of templates managed as part of the user project.

    Templates are identified by name. Each time a template is instantiated, a new instance of SpatialObject (or a sub-class thereof) is created.

    This type can be instantiated in applications and background tasks via dependency injection, using @Inject, @Named etc.
    The @Named annotation can be used to differentiate between different objects of the same type like process data.
    More detailed information including code examples can be found in the documentation of the base class of the application or background task.

      • createFromTemplate

        <T extends SpatialObject> T createFromTemplate(String templateName,
                                               Class<T> clazz)
                                        throws TemplateException
        Like createFromTemplate(String), but with the additional requirement that the returned object match the given type.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the desired template instance
        Parameters:
        templateName - the name of the template to instantiate
        clazz - the required Class the template instance must be equal to or derived from
        Returns:
        An object of a dynamic type compatible with clazz, never null.
        Throws:
        TemplateNotFoundException - if no template with the given name could be found
        TemplateClassException - if the template didn't match the expected type
        TemplateException - if the specified template is invalid
